The queen is already unconfortable here. Note that retreat was not possible. But, under normal conditions, the queen is not trapped: it threats b2, and the knight is pinned. NxN, if I leave him, will exchange it, and he will save the rook. But...
A poisoned pawn. Qc3 maybe was better, since it doesn't unpin the knight (the key). If Rc1, Qxa3, and otherwise, I must offer a queen's exchange, giving him tempo to save the rook.
